#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/languages/kotlin/coroutines.adoc:262
msgid ""
"Spring applications are xref:integration/observability.adoc[instrumented "
"with Micrometer for Observability support].  For tracing support, the "
"current observation is propagated through a `ThreadLocal` for blocking code, "
"or the Reactor `Context` for reactive pipelines. But the current observation "
"also needs to be made available in the execution context of a suspended "
"function. Without that, the current \"traceId\" will not be automatically "
"prepended to logged statements from coroutines."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/languages/kotlin/coroutines.adoc:265
msgid ""
"The "
"{spring-framework-api-kdoc}/spring-core/org.springframework.core/-propagation-context-element/index.html[`PropagationContextElement`] "
"operator generally ensures that the "
"{micrometer-context-propagation-docs}/[Micrometer Context Propagation "
"library] works with Kotlin Coroutines."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/languages/kotlin/coroutines.adoc:270
msgid ""
"It requires the `io.micrometer:context-propagation` dependency and "
"optionally the `org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-coroutines-reactor` "
"one. Automatic context propagation via "
"`CoroutinesUtils#invokeSuspendingFunction` (used by Spring to adapt "
"Coroutines to Reactor `Flux` or `Mono`) can be enabled by invoking "
"`Hooks.enableAutomaticContextPropagation()`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/languages/kotlin/coroutines.adoc:273
msgid ""
"Applications can also use `PropagationContextElement` explicitly to augment "
"the `CoroutineContext` with the context propagation mechanism:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/languages/kotlin/coroutines.adoc:278
msgid ""
"Here, assuming that Micrometer Tracing is configured, the resulting logging "
"statement will show the current \"traceId\" and unlock better observability "
"for your application."
msgstr ""
